<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-18T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="737" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d737">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1717a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-18T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            18, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>239. Reports are current that China has sent a note to Japan making a
                                protest against Japanese soldiers being quartered along Chinese
                                Eastern line. Can you verify these reports? If possible, send early
                                reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>